1
00:01:46,820 --> 00:01:51,900
=The Long Season 7=

2
00:01:52,310 --> 00:01:53,550
Get past him!

3
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,270
Come on!

4
00:01:56,270 --> 00:01:57,720
I'd do better than that.

5
00:01:59,440 --> 00:02:00,590
How many chicken ribs have you had?

6
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:02,630
Stop watching. We're on a stakeout.

7
00:02:03,190 --> 00:02:04,870
I won't ask you to pay.

8
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:07,000
We've been watching it all morning.

9
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,240
I'm almost blind!

10
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:10,080
You two are too gullible.

11
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:11,960
You can't trust Xing Jianchun.

12
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:12,600
Excuse me.

13
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:14,240
Get me a plate of chicken hearts.

14
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:14,910
Coming right up!

15
00:02:16,440 --> 00:02:17,470
You should cut back on them.

16
00:02:17,470 --> 00:02:18,470
They're high in cholesterol.

17
00:02:18,470 --> 00:02:20,160
They're for you because you need them.

18
00:02:21,830 --> 00:02:23,360
Save them for yourself and Xiang.

19
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:24,550
You two can have them at night.

20
00:02:31,550 --> 00:02:32,360
Where are you going?

21
00:02:32,910 --> 00:02:33,360
Take the sketch.

22
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:34,270
I gotta go.

23
00:02:34,270 --> 00:02:34,830
Seriously?

24
00:02:34,830 --> 00:02:35,830
You need that many for number two?

25
00:02:35,830 --> 00:02:37,190
There's still enough for your mouth.

26
00:02:37,190 --> 00:02:39,270
You said no bathroom breaks.

27
00:02:39,270 --> 00:02:40,520
Clearly, you have a double standard.

28
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:41,550
We can't go, but you can!

29
00:02:41,550 --> 00:02:43,190
I'm old, but you're not!

30
00:02:43,190 --> 00:02:44,600
Show some respect!

31
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:46,600
I'm insulin-dependent
and still sticking around.

32
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:47,190
Is there a toilet?

33
00:02:47,190 --> 00:02:47,520
No.

34
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:48,160
- Go ahead.
- There's one over there.

35
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:49,160
Don't poop your pants.

36
00:02:49,630 --> 00:02:51,320
Eyes on the target! Watch closely!

37
00:02:51,720 --> 00:02:53,270
He's a burden.

38
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:56,600
Pass! Come on!

39
00:03:07,440 --> 00:03:08,800
Don't touch anything here.

40
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:09,600
I'll be right back.

41
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:10,240
OK, sure.

42
00:03:14,220 --> 00:03:19,100
(China Sports Lottery)

43
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:27,910
Whatever.

44
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:29,520
Here are my numbers.

45
00:03:39,750 --> 00:03:40,750
Do you need anything else?

46
00:03:41,270 --> 00:03:43,160
Maybe a few scratch-off lottery tickets?

47
00:03:43,160 --> 00:03:45,720
They're boring, not challenging at all.

48
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:46,830
But it's a quick game.

49
00:03:46,830 --> 00:03:48,320
You'll know the result right away.

50
00:03:48,320 --> 00:03:49,240
Fine, I'll take one.

51
00:03:51,030 --> 00:03:51,800
Here you are. And your change.

52
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:52,630
Do it for fun.

53
00:03:57,720 --> 00:03:58,750
Has anyone got lucky today?

54
00:03:58,750 --> 00:03:59,360
Yeah.

55
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:00,080
How many?

56
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:01,160
Two.

57
00:04:01,160 --> 00:04:02,880
Why didn't you tell me?

58
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:04,270
The third is doomed to fail.

59
00:04:04,270 --> 00:04:05,520
I won't win anything.

60
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:07,440
Maybe you'll get lucky, too.

61
00:04:07,440 --> 00:04:09,190
Now, I regret it.

62
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,030
Hello.

63
00:04:11,030 --> 00:04:12,320
A ticket of ten yuan.

64
00:04:12,320 --> 00:04:13,080
Got it.

65
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:14,270
All quick picks.

66
00:04:14,270 --> 00:04:15,080
No problem.

67
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:17,480
Quick picks are lame.

68
00:04:17,480 --> 00:04:18,760
You're wasting your money.

69
00:04:19,790 --> 00:04:20,720
You don't own the generator.

70
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:22,760
Would the owner let you win?

71
00:04:24,510 --> 00:04:26,920
You picked the numbers yourself,
but have you ever won?

72
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:28,510
And have you?

73
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:30,720
Me?

74
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:31,640
Listen,

75
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:35,000
I got my car and apartment because of
those quick picks, you know?

76
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:36,000
Come off it!

77
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:37,110
Who knows if that's true?

78
00:04:38,390 --> 00:04:41,070
Dude, here's a piece of advice.

79
00:04:41,070 --> 00:04:44,880
Keep calm and sincere
before getting the tickets.

80
00:04:46,040 --> 00:04:47,110
Loser.

81
00:04:48,880 --> 00:04:50,200
He wouldn't listen.

82
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:51,350
How stubborn!

83
00:04:52,670 --> 00:04:53,760
A ticket of quick picks, too.

84
00:04:57,620 --> 00:05:01,860
(For Hire)

85
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:20,000
Traffic Police Station.

86
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:22,440
Sorry, try another one.

87
00:05:22,440 --> 00:05:23,480
I'm unavailable.

88
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:24,790
I insist.

89
00:05:24,790 --> 00:05:25,670
Come on.

90
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:29,480
What do you want?

91
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:32,270
You tell me.

92
00:05:32,270 --> 00:05:33,350
I gotta go.

93
00:05:33,350 --> 00:05:34,510
Would you rather abandon your car?

94
00:05:34,510 --> 00:05:35,350
Where are you going?

95
00:05:35,350 --> 00:05:36,390
Wait, sir...

96
00:05:36,390 --> 00:05:37,350
Are you so rich?

97
00:05:37,350 --> 00:05:38,640
Easy, man, easy...

98
00:05:38,640 --> 00:05:41,390
Those quick picks
got you a car and an apartment, huh?

99
00:05:41,390 --> 00:05:42,160
Please...

100
00:05:42,160 --> 00:05:43,320
Don't try to fight me.

101
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:44,070
I'm a fighter.

102
00:05:44,070 --> 00:05:45,270
Are you still mad about the quick picks?

103
00:05:45,270 --> 00:05:46,480
This is uncalled for.

104
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:47,270
Shut up!

105
00:05:47,270 --> 00:05:47,640
I'm telling you,

106
00:05:47,640 --> 00:05:49,950
I broke my arm in a brawl. Go easy!

107
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:51,600
Hey, don't...

108
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:52,600
Don't do this.

109
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:53,880
No need to call your gang.

110
00:05:53,880 --> 00:05:54,720
I'm not.

111
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:56,040
I can handle you alone.

112
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:57,480
You know MMA?

113
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:58,950
You're nowhere near my level.

114
00:05:58,950 --> 00:06:01,110
I can flatten you no problem.

115
00:06:01,110 --> 00:06:02,320
Are you done?

116
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:04,720
I found him. Come over now!

117
00:06:08,350 --> 00:06:09,920
Stop it, man.

118
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:11,270
I got nothing in my pockets.

119
00:06:11,270 --> 00:06:12,830
I haven't had any clients.

120
00:06:13,790 --> 00:06:15,950
What? We aren't robbers!

121
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:20,760
So you aren't here for money?

122
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:22,440
Here's my piece of advice.

123
00:06:22,440 --> 00:06:24,390
Answer our questions honestly, got it?

124
00:06:25,070 --> 00:06:26,000
You said and I quote,

125
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:28,200
"Keep calm and sincere".

126
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:31,720
Gentlemen, is there a mistake?

127
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:32,600
I don't think we have a history.

128
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:33,550
What is this?

129
00:06:34,950 --> 00:06:35,880
Not at all.

130
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:37,550
You're the one.

131
00:06:39,510 --> 00:06:40,790
Do I know you?

132
00:06:40,790 --> 00:06:41,760
Cornfield, remember?

133
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:44,000
You were running fast.

134
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:45,200
Were you afraid after the hit-and-run?

135
00:06:45,950 --> 00:06:47,230
What are you talking about?

136
00:06:47,230 --> 00:06:48,720
When did I hit others?

137
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:50,110
Let me remind you.

138
00:06:50,790 --> 00:06:53,390
That morning on October 20th,
you were driving this car

139
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:56,550
with a fake plate of HUAAW357F.

140
00:06:56,550 --> 00:06:57,510
Does that ring a bell?

141
00:06:58,670 --> 00:07:02,640
Look, sir, yes, I don't have
a taxi license, but I'm not a mob.

142
00:07:02,640 --> 00:07:04,350
I wouldn't dare hit anyone.

143
00:07:04,350 --> 00:07:07,350
Look, none of us here is a cop.

144
00:07:07,350 --> 00:07:08,790
Well, even if you said you were,

145
00:07:08,790 --> 00:07:09,790
I wouldn't buy it.

146
00:07:09,790 --> 00:07:10,830
Shut it!

147
00:07:10,830 --> 00:07:11,230
Hey!

148
00:07:11,230 --> 00:07:12,040
Calm down. Ask him nicely.

149
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:14,070
Just answer the question.

150
00:07:14,070 --> 00:07:15,070
What happened?

151
00:07:15,880 --> 00:07:16,670
It's simple.

152
00:07:16,670 --> 00:07:20,000
You aren't our target,
but the one you hit.

153
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,440
I'll say it again.

154
00:07:21,440 --> 00:07:22,510
I didn't hit anyone.

155
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:23,760
Come on!

156
00:07:23,760 --> 00:07:25,390
Stop denying!

157
00:07:25,390 --> 00:07:27,390
We wouldn't be here without evidence.

158
00:07:28,440 --> 00:07:31,160
Your hit-and-run is undeniable.

159
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:34,640
Tell us who the victim is
and we'll let you go.

160
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:38,000
Still feigning calm?

161
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,510
Stop hitting me!

162
00:07:40,790 --> 00:07:42,070
Go ahead, Biao.

163
00:07:42,070 --> 00:07:42,880
OK.

164
00:07:43,790 --> 00:07:45,200
No, put your knife back!

165
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:46,000
No more blood!

166
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:46,550
I'll kill him!

167
00:07:46,550 --> 00:07:47,440
Sir, come on,

168
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:48,200
I respect seniors like you.

169
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:49,670
Please be nice.

170
00:07:53,270 --> 00:07:54,270
You still won't talk?

171
00:07:55,270 --> 00:07:55,920
What to do?

172
00:07:57,830 --> 00:07:58,440
Report him to the police.

173
00:07:59,160 --> 00:08:00,920
You're done. You're over for good.

174
00:08:01,380 --> 00:08:03,300
(Pause)

175
00:08:03,830 --> 00:08:04,390
OK.

176
00:08:04,390 --> 00:08:05,760
(Traffic Police)
Thanks for your help.

177
00:08:06,790 --> 00:08:07,350
Officer...

178
00:08:07,350 --> 00:08:08,390
No need to thank us.

179
00:08:08,390 --> 00:08:11,230
We're on the same side,
so I'll be straight with you.

180
00:08:11,230 --> 00:08:12,790
When can I get my cab back?

181
00:08:12,790 --> 00:08:13,230
Alright.

182
00:08:13,230 --> 00:08:14,350
Go to the Accident Section
for the paperwork.

183
00:08:14,350 --> 00:08:15,040
Thank you!

184
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:17,670
Sir, other than using a fake plate,
he must've done something else.

185
00:08:17,670 --> 00:08:20,070
Can you ask him who he hit?

186
00:08:20,070 --> 00:08:21,270
Don't worry.

187
00:08:21,270 --> 00:08:23,110
A hit-and-run is a serious crime.

188
00:08:23,110 --> 00:08:24,920
We'll get to the bottom of it.

189
00:08:24,920 --> 00:08:25,790
I'll let you know when we find out.

190
00:08:25,790 --> 00:08:26,070
Thanks.

191
00:08:26,070 --> 00:08:26,720
Go home.

192
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:27,270
OK.

193
00:08:27,270 --> 00:08:28,350
Please keep me updated.

194
00:08:28,350 --> 00:08:28,760
Sure.

195
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:30,040
I'm Wang Xiang,

196
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:30,790
"Xiang" as "loud".

197
00:08:30,790 --> 00:08:31,390
Yeah, yeah, got it.

198
00:08:33,150 --> 00:08:37,350
Wang Xiang, what are you up to?

199
00:08:45,150 --> 00:08:46,400
One plate of mutton.

200
00:08:47,030 --> 00:08:48,280
Is there any seafood?

201
00:08:48,960 --> 00:08:49,960
There's calamari.

202
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:50,910
OK, that, too.

203
00:08:50,910 --> 00:08:52,760
There's too much for us.

204
00:08:52,760 --> 00:08:53,760
Not at all.

205
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:54,710
And spicy bellflower root, too.

206
00:08:55,520 --> 00:08:56,790
That's all. We might add more later.

207
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:57,550
OK.

208
00:09:06,440 --> 00:09:07,230
If you two don't propose a toast,

209
00:09:07,230 --> 00:09:08,550
I will.

210
00:09:08,550 --> 00:09:09,910
There's no booze.

211
00:09:09,910 --> 00:09:11,200
Here it is.

212
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:11,840
Your cup, Xiang.

213
00:09:13,880 --> 00:09:15,880
This is a treat mostly
to thank Captain Ma.

214
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:16,320
Yes.

215
00:09:17,280 --> 00:09:18,520
Without you,

216
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:20,550
I wouldn't have got
my cab back so quickly.

217
00:09:20,550 --> 00:09:21,550
No need to thank me.

218
00:09:21,550 --> 00:09:24,080
They found out you're innocent
and gave your car back, of course.

219
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:25,320
No, you should take the credit.

220
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:28,660
Without your help, it wouldn't
have wrapped up so soon, right?

221
00:09:28,660 --> 00:09:28,970
Yep.

222
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:31,150
Let's drink.

223
00:09:31,150 --> 00:09:31,590
Cheers.

224
00:09:39,710 --> 00:09:40,470
Dig in.

225
00:09:44,790 --> 00:09:45,960
What about you?

226
00:09:46,590 --> 00:09:47,840
Aren't you gonna say something?

227
00:09:50,910 --> 00:09:51,880
Come on.

228
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:54,910
Thank you, Captain Ma.

229
00:09:54,910 --> 00:09:55,880
Not that.

230
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:57,150
Say something else.

231
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:01,670
Like what?

232
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:04,400
The truth, of course.

233
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:08,760
Xiang, Captain Ma is a friend.

234
00:10:08,760 --> 00:10:10,030
Just say it.

235
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:15,080
I'm not sure about anything,
so let it go.

236
00:10:15,080 --> 00:10:16,590
Let's eat if you're done drinking.

237
00:10:16,590 --> 00:10:17,590
I'll say it.

238
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:21,110
Who was the guy
that got hit by that fake-licensed car?

239
00:10:22,230 --> 00:10:26,200
Why did you go to such great lengths
to find him?

240
00:10:33,110 --> 00:10:36,000
Be honest with me if we're friends.

241
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:45,440
You've put it like that,

242
00:10:46,400 --> 00:10:52,320
OK, you might not believe this,
but the victim of that hit-and-run

243
00:10:54,280 --> 00:10:55,760
killed my son, Yang.

244
00:10:57,520 --> 00:10:58,670
Unbelievable, right?

245
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:02,590
Yes.

246
00:11:03,760 --> 00:11:04,790
Go on.

247
00:11:11,760 --> 00:11:12,400
I got him on tape.

248
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:28,230
I don't see his face.

249
00:11:28,230 --> 00:11:29,550
How could you be sure it's him?

250
00:11:31,150 --> 00:11:31,710
See?

251
00:11:33,470 --> 00:11:38,280
You didn't believe me then,
and you don't believe me now.

252
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:39,760
So what's the point?

253
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:41,470
I wish I could believe you.

254
00:11:42,110 --> 00:11:46,000
Wang Xiang,
your son's death has driven you nuts.

255
00:11:46,710 --> 00:11:49,320
Are you nuts, too?

256
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:50,280
No, Captain Ma.

257
00:11:50,280 --> 00:11:50,670
It's him that...

258
00:11:50,670 --> 00:11:52,440
Look, the truth is still unknown.

259
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:54,150
How could I let it go?

260
00:11:54,150 --> 00:11:57,590
Wang Yang killed himself
just like I told you 18 years ago.

261
00:11:57,590 --> 00:11:58,760
That's not true.

262
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:00,550
I know my boy.

263
00:12:00,550 --> 00:12:02,960
He was killed by Fu Weijun.

264
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:04,000
Not again!

265
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:07,080
Don't you remember when you were
at the railway, we had caught

266
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:08,470
Fu Weijun.

267
00:12:08,470 --> 00:12:09,790
But how could he get there?

268
00:12:09,790 --> 00:12:11,200
That's why he didn't do it!

269
00:12:15,910 --> 00:12:21,280
You could doubt me, but when he got
caught, everyone saw it right there!

270
00:12:21,280 --> 00:12:22,320
They can't all be wrong!

271
00:12:22,320 --> 00:12:23,640
You are wrong!

272
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:24,200
As you were

273
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:26,110
18 years ago!

274
00:12:26,110 --> 00:12:26,840
Calm down, both of you.

275
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:27,910
Shut up!

276
00:12:27,910 --> 00:12:28,880
Tell me,

277
00:12:28,880 --> 00:12:30,320
Fu Weijun is still in prison.

278
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:31,840
How could he get hit by a car?

279
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:34,150
You tell me how my son died!

280
00:12:34,150 --> 00:12:35,670
Don't raise your voice at us!

281
00:12:35,670 --> 00:12:37,470
Do you think the police would tell lies?

282
00:12:37,470 --> 00:12:40,400
Our work is based on evidence,
not imagination!

283
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:41,470
Is that also my imagination?

284
00:12:41,470 --> 00:12:42,880
Isn't that evidence, hard evidence?

285
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:43,760
I don't see it!

286
00:12:43,760 --> 00:12:44,640
Not his face, not anything!

287
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:46,550
It's your pure imagination!

288
00:12:46,550 --> 00:12:47,590
It's all in your head,

289
00:12:47,590 --> 00:12:48,350
I'm telling you!

290
00:12:48,350 --> 00:12:49,470
It's OK, guys.

291
00:12:49,470 --> 00:12:50,520
Don't be scared. Sorry.

292
00:12:51,230 --> 00:12:52,590
Don't mind them.

293
00:12:52,590 --> 00:12:54,150
Sorry about it.

294
00:12:54,150 --> 00:12:55,150
They're drunk.

295
00:12:57,030 --> 00:12:58,280
Come on, guys.

296
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:00,280
You're too old to make a scene.

297
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:01,280
Act your age.

298
00:13:02,350 --> 00:13:03,670
We can talk at home.

299
00:13:04,790 --> 00:13:08,520
Wang Xiang, think about what I said.

300
00:13:09,280 --> 00:13:13,080
If you're still so obsessed and won't let go,
your life will be ruined.

301
00:13:13,910 --> 00:13:15,000
We've all lost our loved ones.

302
00:13:17,080 --> 00:13:20,200
My wife died of cancer last year.

303
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:21,670
Then what? I should die, too?

304
00:13:21,670 --> 00:13:23,230
It's not the same, OK?

305
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:26,790
Your wife died of disease.

306
00:13:26,790 --> 00:13:30,960
She died on her bed in the hospital
and she could rest in peace.

307
00:13:30,960 --> 00:13:33,710
But my son was not even 20
and he was found in the water!

308
00:13:33,710 --> 00:13:35,760
How could I let it go?

309
00:14:05,030 --> 00:14:05,840
It's OK...

310
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:18,230
Do you still want these?

311
00:14:18,230 --> 00:14:19,640
What do you think?

312
00:14:20,150 --> 00:14:20,790
Can I return them?

313
00:14:20,790 --> 00:14:22,000
No, sorry, sir.

314
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,350
Pack them up.

315
00:14:36,900 --> 00:14:43,900
(Hualin Taxi Pause)

316
00:15:16,110 --> 00:15:17,400
What's that attitude?

317
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:19,000
I'm here for a solution,

318
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:19,320
OK?

319
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:20,230
I've been nothing but nice.

320
00:15:20,230 --> 00:15:21,110
What do you want?

321
00:15:21,110 --> 00:15:22,470
We want money, compensation!

322
00:15:22,470 --> 00:15:23,400
Hey, guys...

323
00:15:23,400 --> 00:15:23,910
Hey,

324
00:15:24,760 --> 00:15:26,150
Ms. Xu, right?

325
00:15:26,150 --> 00:15:27,550
What's wrong? You got a sty?

326
00:15:27,550 --> 00:15:29,910
No! Shut up!

327
00:15:29,910 --> 00:15:33,110
My eyes got double eyelids,
but look what your wife did!

328
00:15:33,110 --> 00:15:34,440
A single and a double.

329
00:15:34,440 --> 00:15:35,470
I can fix the single one.

330
00:15:35,470 --> 00:15:36,350
No problem.

331
00:15:36,350 --> 00:15:36,670
Yeah.

332
00:15:36,670 --> 00:15:41,030
Just fix that eye for free as a gift.

333
00:15:41,030 --> 00:15:42,640
That's not gonna happen.

334
00:15:42,640 --> 00:15:44,030
What if you blind her?

335
00:15:44,550 --> 00:15:46,440
It's cold. We can talk inside.

336
00:15:46,440 --> 00:15:47,030
Why?

337
00:15:47,030 --> 00:15:48,520
Are you afraid 'cause you're unlicensed?

338
00:15:48,520 --> 00:15:49,280
Of course not.

339
00:15:49,280 --> 00:15:50,280
Our business is legit.

340
00:15:50,280 --> 00:15:51,110
Is that so?

341
00:15:51,110 --> 00:15:52,030
Is there a license?

342
00:15:52,030 --> 00:15:53,000
It's being processed.

343
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:54,200
So no!

344
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:55,230
We'll get it soon.

345
00:15:55,230 --> 00:15:56,790
Very soon.

346
00:15:56,790 --> 00:15:59,790
You're breaking the law, you know?

347
00:15:59,790 --> 00:16:02,000
Ms. Xu, think about it.

348
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:04,840
If you go to any big hospital to do your eyes,
it'll cost six grand, right?

349
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:05,400
But here

350
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:06,960
I asked for two grand
plus ten percent off.

351
00:16:06,960 --> 00:16:08,520
You got what you paid for,

352
00:16:08,520 --> 00:16:09,790
OK?

353
00:16:09,790 --> 00:16:11,110
You mean I had it coming?

354
00:16:11,110 --> 00:16:11,910
I deserve it?

355
00:16:11,910 --> 00:16:12,640
I didn't say that.

356
00:16:12,640 --> 00:16:13,150
Listen...

357
00:16:13,150 --> 00:16:13,640
Enough.

358
00:16:13,640 --> 00:16:14,470
Are you picking a fight?

359
00:16:14,470 --> 00:16:15,440
Say no more.

360
00:16:15,440 --> 00:16:16,350
Call the cops.

361
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:16,790
Please don't!

362
00:16:16,790 --> 00:16:17,640
Don't trouble the police.

363
00:16:17,640 --> 00:16:18,320
Come on!

364
00:16:18,910 --> 00:16:20,550
We can talk it out ourselves.

365
00:16:21,640 --> 00:16:22,910
Pay for her damage.

366
00:16:24,030 --> 00:16:25,640
It's not about the money.

367
00:16:27,110 --> 00:16:28,760
But if you insist,

368
00:16:28,760 --> 00:16:29,590
I'd say 150k.

369
00:16:29,590 --> 00:16:30,230
Come again?

370
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:32,280
150k.

371
00:16:32,280 --> 00:16:33,350
That's extortion!

372
00:16:33,350 --> 00:16:34,670
What did you say?

373
00:16:34,670 --> 00:16:36,000
You're extorting me!

374
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:38,150
150k is the least.

375
00:16:38,150 --> 00:16:40,910
If I'm blind, you'll go to jail!

376
00:16:40,910 --> 00:16:41,440
Calm down.

377
00:16:42,030 --> 00:16:45,230
Look, we all worked in the same factory.

378
00:16:45,230 --> 00:16:47,000
Don't be too harsh.

379
00:16:47,760 --> 00:16:49,790
Maybe a discount for old times' sake?

380
00:16:49,790 --> 00:16:51,030
How about 10k?

381
00:16:51,030 --> 00:16:52,000
Give me the phone.

382
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:52,640
Call it in.

383
00:16:52,640 --> 00:16:56,080
Who are you to think you're worth 140k?

384
00:16:56,910 --> 00:16:58,320
Fine. Make the call!

385
00:16:59,030 --> 00:17:00,670
Let the cops grab her
and give her ten years.

386
00:17:00,670 --> 00:17:01,320
Go ahead.

387
00:17:04,470 --> 00:17:06,590
Let's see if you'll get
any money from us.

388
00:17:06,590 --> 00:17:07,520
Think about it.

389
00:17:12,760 --> 00:17:14,920
We can talk it over.

390
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:18,280
She charged 1.8k,
and now, you're asking for 150k?

391
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:19,280
Why not make it a billion?

392
00:17:19,280 --> 00:17:20,230
Like I had it.

393
00:17:20,230 --> 00:17:21,640
So be practical.

394
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:22,800
How about this?

395
00:17:22,800 --> 00:17:23,640
She paid you 1.8k, right?

396
00:17:23,640 --> 00:17:26,470
So give that back plus 30k damages.

397
00:17:26,470 --> 00:17:27,560
Am I that cheap?

398
00:17:27,560 --> 00:17:28,830
Do I look like a beggar?

399
00:17:28,830 --> 00:17:30,110
Give me the phone. I'm calling it!

400
00:17:32,230 --> 00:17:33,560
Name your price.

401
00:17:37,280 --> 00:17:37,800
100k.

402
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:38,710
I don't have it...

403
00:17:38,710 --> 00:17:40,710
No bargaining, or we're done here!

404
00:17:41,470 --> 00:17:44,680
Okay, 100k with a signed note.

405
00:17:44,680 --> 00:17:46,430
Then there's no coming back!

406
00:17:52,190 --> 00:17:53,350
Be careful.

407
00:17:55,760 --> 00:17:56,520
Good day.

408
00:17:58,190 --> 00:17:59,880
Sorry, ma'am.

409
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:00,920
See you, ma'am.

410
00:18:01,950 --> 00:18:03,920
Stop calling me ma'am!

411
00:18:03,920 --> 00:18:05,230
You look much older than me!

412
00:18:05,230 --> 00:18:07,430
Pay up this week,
or I'll see you at the police station.

413
00:18:07,430 --> 00:18:08,470
Yes, ma'am.

414
00:18:10,040 --> 00:18:11,880
Eyes on the road. Hold her.

415
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:31,070
Hey, dude,

416
00:18:31,070 --> 00:18:32,520
I'd like to sell my license.

417
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:33,590
Ask around for me.

418
00:18:33,950 --> 00:18:35,000
What's it worth?

419
00:18:36,280 --> 00:18:37,190
It's getting lower?

420
00:18:37,880 --> 00:18:39,110
100k is fine.

421
00:18:39,110 --> 00:18:40,110
I need cash.

422
00:18:41,760 --> 00:18:42,430
Call me if there's a buyer.

423
00:18:54,350 --> 00:18:55,310
Had too much corn.

424
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:14,710
Come on.

425
00:19:15,680 --> 00:19:17,070
There, there.

426
00:19:17,710 --> 00:19:18,950
I'm not blaming you.

427
00:19:20,160 --> 00:19:22,070
And we've had it solved.

428
00:19:22,070 --> 00:19:23,040
It's OK.

429
00:19:23,040 --> 00:19:26,560
Where could I get 100k?

430
00:19:26,560 --> 00:19:28,470
No worries. I'll handle it.

431
00:19:28,470 --> 00:19:30,070
Easy-peasy.

432
00:19:30,070 --> 00:19:32,070
It's all your fault!

433
00:19:32,070 --> 00:19:34,430
You bought that license behind my back.

434
00:19:34,430 --> 00:19:35,560
Hadn't it been for you,

435
00:19:35,560 --> 00:19:39,590
I would've rented a shop
and none of this would've happened!

436
00:19:46,430 --> 00:19:47,560
It's OK. Everything will be fine.

437
00:19:47,560 --> 00:19:48,560
Don't touch me!

438
00:19:51,070 --> 00:19:52,590
Money goes and comes.

439
00:19:53,190 --> 00:19:55,000
Once my pigeons for racing are hatched,

440
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:57,160
I'll gain
tens of thousands by selling them.

441
00:19:57,800 --> 00:19:59,920
It's no big deal if money can fix it.

442
00:19:59,920 --> 00:20:00,880
Am I right?

443
00:20:06,310 --> 00:20:09,040
How did we mess up so bad?

444
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:12,950
Don't be upset.

445
00:20:14,110 --> 00:20:17,470
Once my pigeons lay eggs,
things will pick up.

446
00:20:18,280 --> 00:20:22,590
We're going from primitive accumulation
to crossing class lines

447
00:20:22,830 --> 00:20:24,350
toward financial freedom.

448
00:20:24,350 --> 00:20:25,640
You know what that means?

449
00:20:26,190 --> 00:20:28,520
Money is working for you,
not the other way around.

450
00:20:28,520 --> 00:20:30,110
Make money with money, got it?

451
00:20:35,040 --> 00:20:39,920
I wish I could be like you
always living in your dreams.

452
00:20:40,520 --> 00:20:41,920
Is that bad?

453
00:20:41,920 --> 00:20:44,800
Dreams are a reflection of reality.

454
00:20:44,800 --> 00:20:45,880
Freud said that.

455
00:20:46,920 --> 00:20:49,830
Biao, we should separate.

456
00:21:13,950 --> 00:21:15,760
Bei's not at home. I'll take his room.

457
00:21:16,560 --> 00:21:18,400
I'm not sure if he'll agree.

458
00:21:19,470 --> 00:21:20,760
It's comfy. Try it.

459
00:21:25,640 --> 00:21:27,310
I can't stretch my legs.

460
00:21:27,310 --> 00:21:29,230
It's two-meter-long.

461
00:21:29,230 --> 00:21:30,230
What about your room?

462
00:21:30,230 --> 00:21:31,110
We can share a bed.

463
00:21:31,110 --> 00:21:32,710
No way. I wake up easily.

464
00:21:33,710 --> 00:21:35,830
Your teeth grinding, farts,
and smacks are nonstop.

465
00:21:35,830 --> 00:21:36,590
I can't take that!

466
00:21:37,070 --> 00:21:39,950
But I'm a guest,
not to mention we're related.

467
00:21:40,640 --> 00:21:42,880
I'm heartbreaking because of Liru.

468
00:21:42,880 --> 00:21:44,280
Can't you be nice to me?

469
00:21:45,110 --> 00:21:48,350
If you two divorce,
we'll be mere coworkers.

470
00:21:48,350 --> 00:21:49,040
What are you doing?

471
00:21:49,920 --> 00:21:50,470
Smoke in the kitchen.

472
00:21:53,560 --> 00:21:55,040
I'll go to the bathroom.

473
00:21:56,070 --> 00:21:56,880
Even better.

474
00:21:58,160 --> 00:21:59,350
Grab a pillow, will you?

475
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:02,110
Wash your feet before bed.

476
00:22:02,110 --> 00:22:03,070
You stink.

477
00:22:15,430 --> 00:22:16,310
What brings you here?

478
00:22:17,190 --> 00:22:18,160
Am I unwelcome?

479
00:22:20,040 --> 00:22:21,280
I'll get you a towel.

480
00:22:24,950 --> 00:22:25,590
Biao?

481
00:22:25,590 --> 00:22:27,070
What? I'm pooping!

482
00:22:28,070 --> 00:22:28,920
No need.

483
00:22:29,760 --> 00:22:31,400
I got news about Fu Weijun.

484
00:22:39,190 --> 00:22:41,230
Last month, he died in prison.

485
00:22:44,190 --> 00:22:45,160
He's dead.

486
00:22:47,400 --> 00:22:48,350
Yep.

487
00:22:49,180 --> 00:22:55,100
(Phone Booth)

488
00:23:07,110 --> 00:23:10,430
Page 9532657.

489
00:23:10,430 --> 00:23:11,350
Leave a message.

490
00:23:11,350 --> 00:23:15,640
Weijun and I are now in Songhe.

491
00:23:37,830 --> 00:23:38,430
Sir?

492
00:23:42,230 --> 00:23:42,880
Hey!

493
00:23:44,310 --> 00:23:45,280
Two coins on credit.

494
00:23:46,680 --> 00:23:48,470
No credit.

495
00:23:48,470 --> 00:23:50,520
Pay me or go home.

496
00:23:51,430 --> 00:23:53,880
I'll pay you back
when my parents come back.

497
00:23:53,880 --> 00:23:54,800
Just this once, please.

498
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:55,640
No can do.

499
00:23:55,950 --> 00:23:56,920
Go away.

500
00:24:00,520 --> 00:24:01,190
50 yuan's worth.

501
00:24:09,590 --> 00:24:10,430
What's wrong?

502
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:11,760
No more coins?

503
00:24:17,070 --> 00:24:17,710
Take these.

504
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:19,710
Thank you.

505
00:24:22,190 --> 00:24:25,560
What... what were you playing?

506
00:24:25,560 --> 00:24:26,350
KOF.

507
00:24:29,040 --> 00:24:30,040
Are you good?

508
00:24:30,560 --> 00:24:31,280
I'm OK.

509
00:24:33,160 --> 00:24:36,560
I don't like playing with the machine.

510
00:24:36,560 --> 00:24:38,400
Would you like to join me?

511
00:24:39,400 --> 00:24:41,190
Oh, I...

512
00:24:41,190 --> 00:24:43,430
I'll pay for it.

513
00:24:43,430 --> 00:24:45,350
We'll use my coins.

514
00:24:45,350 --> 00:24:46,160
OK.

515
00:24:46,680 --> 00:24:47,680
I'll insert the coin.

516
00:24:54,230 --> 00:24:55,800
What's... what's your name?

517
00:24:55,800 --> 00:24:56,640
Shen Hui.

518
00:25:13,830 --> 00:25:14,350
Hi.

519
00:25:16,710 --> 00:25:17,680
There you are.

520
00:25:18,880 --> 00:25:20,430
Let's go play games.

521
00:25:20,430 --> 00:25:21,190
I can't.

522
00:25:21,190 --> 00:25:22,470
My mom's waiting for me at home.

523
00:25:24,920 --> 00:25:26,590
You're lying.

524
00:25:27,590 --> 00:25:29,680
Aren't you staying at your grandma's?

525
00:25:32,190 --> 00:25:36,110
Your... your parents
are out of town, aren't they?

526
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:39,560
They've come back?

527
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:44,590
That fast?

528
00:25:46,070 --> 00:25:48,110
I... I really can't go.

529
00:25:48,110 --> 00:25:49,950
My grandma will get worried
if she doesn't see me.

530
00:26:09,070 --> 00:26:12,950
Are you turning your back on me?

531
00:26:15,590 --> 00:26:20,590
You don't see me as...
as a friend, do you?

532
00:26:23,400 --> 00:26:24,070
Fine.

533
00:26:26,190 --> 00:26:30,230
I want my money back for the coins.

534
00:26:30,230 --> 00:26:32,190
I... I don't have any.

535
00:26:33,160 --> 00:26:33,920
I...

536
00:26:35,070 --> 00:26:36,430
I swear.

537
00:26:38,640 --> 00:26:39,880
Now what?

538
00:26:44,920 --> 00:26:47,000
You... you won't find it in my bag.

539
00:26:49,190 --> 00:26:49,680
I've got no money.

540
00:26:49,680 --> 00:26:51,160
Then I'll report you to your teacher!

541
00:26:57,880 --> 00:26:58,430
Hi.

542
00:27:14,560 --> 00:27:20,350
He's asking you what you have

543
00:27:21,430 --> 00:27:23,880
if you've got no money.

544
00:27:29,880 --> 00:27:31,280
What do I have?

545
00:27:32,950 --> 00:27:34,350
So what do you want?

546
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:40,110
So what do you want?

547
00:27:52,710 --> 00:27:57,400
Your arm, or your leg.

548
00:28:04,800 --> 00:28:05,350
Let me go!

549
00:28:05,350 --> 00:28:05,920
Please, let me go!

550
00:28:05,920 --> 00:28:06,830
I'm begging you!

551
00:28:06,830 --> 00:28:07,680
Don't do this!

552
00:28:07,680 --> 00:28:08,800
Please! Don't...!

553
00:28:08,800 --> 00:28:09,590
Please!

554
00:28:09,590 --> 00:28:10,760
Please don't hurt me!

555
00:28:10,760 --> 00:28:11,470
Don't hurt me!

556
00:28:11,470 --> 00:28:13,350
Let me go! I'm begging you!

557
00:28:13,350 --> 00:28:14,430
Please...!

