566
00:28:46,310 --> 00:28:47,560
Is everything OK, Aunt?

567
00:28:49,310 --> 00:28:50,350
What's wrong?

568
00:28:51,350 --> 00:28:52,430
It's all my fault.

569
00:28:53,280 --> 00:28:54,950
I shouldn't have come here
to see the doctor.

570
00:28:54,950 --> 00:28:57,190
Or Hui wouldn't have gotten hurt.

571
00:28:57,190 --> 00:28:58,160
Quit it!

572
00:29:02,640 --> 00:29:03,590
I'll check out the room.

573
00:29:39,310 --> 00:29:41,230
Don't be too worried.

574
00:29:41,230 --> 00:29:42,560
A broken arm isn't too bad.

575
00:29:42,560 --> 00:29:43,280
It'll heal.

576
00:29:48,190 --> 00:29:48,950
Excuse me?

577
00:29:51,040 --> 00:29:54,160
But next time,
he might not be this lucky.

578
00:29:54,160 --> 00:29:55,880
Go home and take care of my aunt.

579
00:29:55,880 --> 00:29:56,950
Don't ever come back.

580
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:09,520
I will... kill you!

581
00:30:09,520 --> 00:30:10,760
Mark my words!

582
00:30:26,680 --> 00:30:31,310
I will kill you!

583
00:31:42,590 --> 00:31:44,800
Yang, dinner is ready.

584
00:31:44,800 --> 00:31:45,920
Eat without me, Mom.

585
00:31:53,560 --> 00:31:54,560
Are you OK, Mom?

586
00:31:54,560 --> 00:31:55,190
What's wrong?

587
00:31:56,430 --> 00:31:57,520
I don't feel well.

588
00:32:00,430 --> 00:32:01,310
What is it?

589
00:32:01,310 --> 00:32:02,310
It'll pass.

590
00:32:04,880 --> 00:32:06,430
I just need to eat something.

591
00:32:07,950 --> 00:32:09,310
I can't breathe because of the smoke.

592
00:32:10,400 --> 00:32:11,680
I'll be fine after dinner.

593
00:32:11,680 --> 00:32:12,560
Come on.

594
00:32:12,560 --> 00:32:14,280
Sit and eat with me.

595
00:32:14,280 --> 00:32:14,760
Sit.

596
00:32:17,190 --> 00:32:18,640
They're all your favorites.

597
00:32:29,280 --> 00:32:30,760
Are you still mad at your dad?

598
00:32:38,470 --> 00:32:40,590
He was trying to protect you.

599
00:32:40,590 --> 00:32:44,110
If Xing Jianchun refused to let it go,
you wouldn't get into the factory.

600
00:32:44,110 --> 00:32:46,040
Hurting you is the
last thing he wanna do.

601
00:32:46,040 --> 00:32:48,760
He regretted it so much
that he couldn't sleep last night

602
00:32:48,760 --> 00:32:50,640
and woke up with blisters on his mouth.

603
00:32:52,710 --> 00:32:54,110
How could I not be mad?

604
00:32:55,110 --> 00:32:57,640
He slapped me in front of everyone.

605
00:32:57,640 --> 00:32:59,920
Besides, do I have to work
at the factory?

606
00:32:59,920 --> 00:33:00,640
I know.

607
00:33:01,800 --> 00:33:05,110
So that's decent,
and what I'm doing is not?

608
00:33:06,160 --> 00:33:07,000
All work has equal value.

609
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:09,110
I can't believe he's so snobbish.

610
00:33:12,070 --> 00:33:16,000
About that, you can't blame your dad

611
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:19,070
because our generation
is used to following orders.

612
00:33:20,000 --> 00:33:22,310
We grew up in a big family.

613
00:33:22,310 --> 00:33:24,040
We'd do whatever our parents said.

614
00:33:24,040 --> 00:33:27,560
And when we started working,
we'd do whatever our bosses said.

615
00:33:27,560 --> 00:33:30,710
People like us all seem

616
00:33:30,710 --> 00:33:33,800
to live in a circle drawn by others.

617
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:38,640
And there we are following the direction
and living our life as it is.

618
00:33:38,640 --> 00:33:41,950
Nobody has ever asked why
or tried to step out of it.

619
00:33:41,950 --> 00:33:44,310
We'd be scared even on the edge.

620
00:33:48,070 --> 00:33:50,350
The world is changing rapidly.

621
00:33:50,560 --> 00:33:52,350
Every generation is different.

622
00:33:53,310 --> 00:33:56,880
When you become a father,
you'll have problems, too.

623
00:33:57,710 --> 00:34:00,640
But even so, you'll always be a family.

624
00:34:01,920 --> 00:34:03,710
Don't hate your dad, OK?

625
00:34:05,470 --> 00:34:07,000
I won't.

626
00:34:07,000 --> 00:34:08,870
I'm not that petty.

627
00:34:08,870 --> 00:34:09,600
That's my boy.

628
00:34:10,230 --> 00:34:12,040
Come on. Let's eat.

629
00:34:12,040 --> 00:34:12,840
Dig in.

630
00:34:14,800 --> 00:34:15,320
Eat.

631
00:34:18,150 --> 00:34:18,760
Mom,

632
00:34:20,430 --> 00:34:21,630
I need to go out.

633
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:25,600
Eat something first.

634
00:34:25,600 --> 00:34:26,120
I'm good.

635
00:34:30,870 --> 00:34:31,280
Alright.

636
00:34:31,280 --> 00:34:32,710
Don't be back too late.

637
00:34:34,390 --> 00:34:35,360
I'm off, Mom.

638
00:34:36,910 --> 00:34:37,670
See you later.

639
00:34:52,520 --> 00:34:53,870
Hey, stop.

640
00:34:53,870 --> 00:34:54,840
No late-night screenings today.

641
00:34:55,560 --> 00:34:56,470
I'm here for Shen Mo.

642
00:34:57,040 --> 00:34:58,080
She said she'd come.

643
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:08,230
You're here early.

644
00:35:13,630 --> 00:35:14,470
Titanic?

645
00:35:15,080 --> 00:35:16,360
We didn't get to watch it together.

646
00:35:16,360 --> 00:35:17,910
Let's do it now.

647
00:35:22,950 --> 00:35:24,190
Wang Yang.

648
00:35:26,320 --> 00:35:27,320
Fu Weijun.

649
00:35:28,520 --> 00:35:30,000
Let me see if it works.

650
00:35:48,630 --> 00:35:52,120
Hey, did you and Shen Mo just meet?

651
00:35:52,120 --> 00:35:53,280
She's never told me about you.

652
00:35:56,470 --> 00:35:57,470
I'm talking to you.

653
00:35:59,120 --> 00:36:00,470
He can't hear you.

654
00:36:01,280 --> 00:36:02,760
Oh, I see.

655
00:36:02,760 --> 00:36:04,080
Or there'd be a fight.

656
00:36:25,360 --> 00:36:26,560
What did he say?

657
00:36:26,560 --> 00:36:27,910
My brother said you're a little simple.

658
00:36:37,890 --> 00:36:40,000
(Rose, you're no picnic, alright?)

659
00:36:40,700 --> 00:36:43,120
(You're a spoiled little brat, even.)

660
00:36:43,650 --> 00:36:44,930
(But under that,)

661
00:36:45,310 --> 00:36:49,500
(You're the most amazingly
astounding, wonderful girl,)

662
00:36:49,820 --> 00:36:51,230
(woman that I've ever known.)

663
00:36:52,120 --> 00:36:52,720
(And...)

664
00:36:52,720 --> 00:36:53,550
(Jack, I...)

665
00:36:53,550 --> 00:36:54,660
(No, let me try to get this out.)

666
00:36:56,440 --> 00:36:57,390
(I'm not an idiot.)

667
00:36:58,070 --> 00:36:59,500
(I know how the world works.)

668
00:36:59,900 --> 00:37:01,110
(I've got ten bucks in my pocket.)

669
00:37:01,110 --> 00:37:03,790
(I have nothing to offer you
and I know that.)

670
00:37:04,520 --> 00:37:05,450
(I understand.)

671
00:37:06,360 --> 00:37:07,860
(But I'm too involved now.)

672
00:37:08,800 --> 00:37:10,530
(You jump, I jump, remember?)

673
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:14,360
You're a Shen.

674
00:37:14,360 --> 00:37:15,950
How come your brother is a Fu?

675
00:37:18,150 --> 00:37:19,560
He's one year younger than me.

676
00:37:19,840 --> 00:37:22,760
When our parents passed away,
we first went to my uncle's place.

677
00:37:23,000 --> 00:37:26,560
My aunt didn't want him
because he was deaf

678
00:37:27,390 --> 00:37:29,320
and gave him to a family in Hualin.

679
00:37:29,950 --> 00:37:32,630
They named him Fu Weijun
and he's used to that name.

680
00:37:33,840 --> 00:37:36,910
Then when they had their own kid,
he went to the orphanage.

681
00:37:37,910 --> 00:37:40,390
I wanted to go to college in Hualin
so that I could see him.

682
00:37:40,390 --> 00:37:42,130
(And you're gonna die
if you don't break free.)

683
00:37:42,360 --> 00:37:44,000
He's the only family member I've left.

684
00:37:47,150 --> 00:37:48,840
Now, you've got one more.

685
00:37:59,410 --> 00:38:00,730
(Only you can do that.)

686
00:38:06,700 --> 00:38:07,960
(I'm going back. Leave me alone.)

687
00:38:38,800 --> 00:38:39,430
Cui Guodong!

688
00:38:42,390 --> 00:38:43,320
Down here!

689
00:38:45,840 --> 00:38:47,080
Who found it?

690
00:38:47,080 --> 00:38:48,120
Joint Defense.

691
00:38:48,840 --> 00:38:49,910
It's in the trench.

692
00:38:49,910 --> 00:38:50,320
Let me see.

693
00:38:50,870 --> 00:38:51,390
Careful.

694
00:38:52,470 --> 00:38:53,430
Let me see it!

695
00:38:54,600 --> 00:38:56,040
Make a hole.

696
00:38:56,040 --> 00:38:58,760
Didn't you circle a few drain outlets?

697
00:38:59,280 --> 00:39:03,630
Joint Defense was checking them
and found something here.

698
00:39:04,560 --> 00:39:05,950
Wang Xiang is good.

699
00:39:19,520 --> 00:39:20,320
Are you OK?

700
00:39:23,190 --> 00:39:25,120
Whoever did that is a monster!

701
00:39:33,430 --> 00:39:35,000
There's a bag in the trench, too.

702
00:39:35,870 --> 00:39:37,430
They found a meal card
of Hualin Health Vocational College.

703
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:44,560
Put yourself together. Go back to work.

704
00:39:47,390 --> 00:39:49,470
Get out of here!

705
00:39:53,120 --> 00:39:54,080
Leave no stone unturned.

706
00:40:23,100 --> 00:40:26,140
(Daxiang Film)

707
00:40:28,840 --> 00:40:29,800
Such content is poison.

708
00:40:29,800 --> 00:40:30,950
No wonder he couldn't get into college.

709
00:40:34,340 --> 00:40:36,180
(Alu's Death)

710
00:40:39,280 --> 00:40:40,630
"At this moment,

711
00:40:40,630 --> 00:40:46,280
I'd rather die before my father
and have my mother's elegy

712
00:40:46,280 --> 00:40:50,230
guard me and the four seasons."

713
00:40:51,950 --> 00:40:53,560
What kind of poetry is that?

714
00:40:53,560 --> 00:40:55,000
Nothing rhymes.

715
00:40:59,470 --> 00:41:00,430
Where is it?

716
00:41:18,360 --> 00:41:20,150
Did someone break in?

717
00:41:20,840 --> 00:41:21,280
Dad.

718
00:41:22,040 --> 00:41:23,360
Why do you have a protective suit?

719
00:41:24,080 --> 00:41:25,470
I haven't used it for years.

720
00:41:27,670 --> 00:41:29,910
I wore it when going climbing
with Qu Bo earlier.

721
00:41:30,560 --> 00:41:31,520
It could keep me warm.

722
00:41:31,520 --> 00:41:34,150
Where did you go? A snow mountain?

723
00:41:35,150 --> 00:41:37,520
Where's our old map?

724
00:41:37,520 --> 00:41:38,040
I think

725
00:41:38,040 --> 00:41:39,470
I put it in a cookbook.

726
00:41:39,470 --> 00:41:40,470
It's up there.

727
00:41:43,120 --> 00:41:44,710
Why did you put it that high?

728
00:41:48,120 --> 00:41:50,670
Hey, what do you need the map for?

729
00:41:51,000 --> 00:41:51,870
It's for the dismemberment case.

730
00:41:51,870 --> 00:41:53,760
I'm helping the police
watch over the factory.

731
00:41:54,470 --> 00:41:56,000
I need to have a meeting
with Xing Jianchun.

732
00:41:56,320 --> 00:41:57,910
What about lunch?

733
00:41:57,910 --> 00:42:00,040
Justice prevails over food.

734
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:02,520
What a busybody!

735
00:42:13,630 --> 00:42:14,390
Mr. Wang.

736
00:42:15,230 --> 00:42:17,520
The train will gather rust
if it continues sitting there.

737
00:42:18,560 --> 00:42:19,520
Relax.

738
00:42:20,560 --> 00:42:23,280
There won't be
a single rusty screw cap under my watch.

739
00:42:23,280 --> 00:42:24,190
The train will outlive you.

740
00:42:29,390 --> 00:42:30,840
Isn't that Security's thermos?

741
00:42:30,840 --> 00:42:31,910
Did they transfer you there?

742
00:42:33,000 --> 00:42:36,230
I'm working on something else
and teaching the staff of Security.

743
00:42:36,760 --> 00:42:37,710
You're teaching them?

744
00:42:38,560 --> 00:42:40,390
I should find time
to teach you guys, too.

745
00:42:41,280 --> 00:42:42,910
My lecture will be:

746
00:42:42,910 --> 00:42:45,560
Keep Guard Up and Eyes Open.

747
00:43:11,600 --> 00:43:13,040
Where are their manners?

748
00:43:17,080 --> 00:43:17,800
Mr. Wang.

749
00:43:17,800 --> 00:43:19,150
(Meeting at 1 p.m.!)

750
00:43:19,150 --> 00:43:21,390
You're leaving? What about the meeting?

751
00:43:22,120 --> 00:43:22,710
Where is everyone?

752
00:43:23,710 --> 00:43:24,470
We're supposed to begin at 1 p.m.

753
00:43:24,470 --> 00:43:25,430
Where are your people?

754
00:43:27,560 --> 00:43:28,390
Look,

755
00:43:28,390 --> 00:43:30,630
I just got a call from Mr. Ma.

756
00:43:30,630 --> 00:43:33,430
He asked me to work with you
on the internal investigation.

757
00:43:33,430 --> 00:43:36,430
Now, I know what to do.

758
00:43:36,430 --> 00:43:37,390
Save it...

759
00:43:37,910 --> 00:43:41,040
Speaking of this matter,
here's what I think.

760
00:43:41,040 --> 00:43:44,360
Well, actually,

761
00:43:47,000 --> 00:43:49,630
I think we're zeroing in on him.

762
00:43:53,040 --> 00:43:54,040
Who is that?

763
00:43:54,040 --> 00:43:58,150
Not sure yet, but I think
the killer did show up here.

764
00:44:04,150 --> 00:44:05,710
You know why nobody came?

765
00:44:13,710 --> 00:44:15,230
They're all on stakeouts.

766
00:44:16,190 --> 00:44:17,040
Stakeouts?

767
00:44:17,040 --> 00:44:17,760
That's right.

768
00:44:23,910 --> 00:44:24,760
So?

769
00:44:24,760 --> 00:44:25,670
Found anything?

770
00:44:26,230 --> 00:44:26,870
Nothing yet.

771
00:44:27,670 --> 00:44:31,760
Dazhi, tell Mr. Wang
what you saw that night.

772
00:44:33,630 --> 00:44:35,430
So the other night,

773
00:44:35,430 --> 00:44:40,150
I finished my shift and
brought my stuff to shower.

774
00:44:40,150 --> 00:44:45,190
Then I passed the furnaces
and kept going and going.

775
00:44:45,190 --> 00:44:46,280
Suddenly,

776
00:44:47,470 --> 00:44:48,950
I heard something.

777
00:44:51,280 --> 00:44:52,150
Like what?

778
00:44:52,150 --> 00:44:55,280
I stopped, he stopped.

779
00:44:55,870 --> 00:44:57,520
I walked, he walked.

780
00:44:58,910 --> 00:45:01,120
Then I looked over toward the furnaces.

781
00:45:02,470 --> 00:45:03,470
What did you see?

782
00:45:03,470 --> 00:45:06,760
I saw a guy in full protective clothing
standing above the furnace.

783
00:45:07,630 --> 00:45:10,800
Then he turned around, faceless.

784
00:45:13,120 --> 00:45:14,360
Faceless?

785
00:45:15,600 --> 00:45:16,710
I don't buy it.

786
00:45:16,710 --> 00:45:17,950
If I lied,

787
00:45:17,950 --> 00:45:18,870
I'd be a pig.

788
00:45:20,120 --> 00:45:23,910
If you couldn't see his face, how
could you be sure that he's the killer?

789
00:45:23,910 --> 00:45:24,800
I...

790
00:45:24,800 --> 00:45:27,520
About that, think about it.

791
00:45:27,520 --> 00:45:30,040
That guy cut a human in pieces.

792
00:45:30,040 --> 00:45:31,230
He's more than ruthless.

793
00:45:31,230 --> 00:45:33,360
You can pick up his murderous vibes!

794
00:45:33,360 --> 00:45:34,150
Dazhi saw it.

795
00:45:34,150 --> 00:45:35,280
You saw it, didn't you?

796
00:45:35,280 --> 00:45:35,950
See?

797
00:45:39,150 --> 00:45:42,000
So you didn't see anything
but his murderous vibes.

798
00:45:42,910 --> 00:45:43,840
I'm serious.

799
00:45:43,840 --> 00:45:44,560
You two may leave.

800
00:45:46,320 --> 00:45:47,150
Wang Xiang,

801
00:45:47,150 --> 00:45:52,430
I'm telling you, he's come once, and
it's possible that he'll come again.

802
00:45:53,280 --> 00:45:55,360
I've mobilized everyone in my section.

803
00:45:56,000 --> 00:46:00,320
Every entrance of every factory
and the main roads is now under watch.

804
00:46:00,320 --> 00:46:03,950
We're looking for a male under 1.8 meters
with murderous vibes.

805
00:46:04,670 --> 00:46:07,950
A male under 1.8 meters
with murderous vibes.

806
00:46:07,950 --> 00:46:11,760
We've got hundreds of them
if not a thousand as poverty can bring out

807
00:46:11,760 --> 00:46:12,670
the worst in people.

808
00:46:15,710 --> 00:46:18,760
Wang Xiang, you're a senior worker.

809
00:46:18,760 --> 00:46:20,840
You should set an example.

810
00:46:20,840 --> 00:46:24,600
Steel-making Shop is
where the suspect was first spotted.

811
00:46:24,600 --> 00:46:26,560
I want you to watch it.

812
00:46:27,390 --> 00:46:27,910
Why?

813
00:46:27,910 --> 00:46:29,230
Why not report it to Captain Ma?

814
00:46:29,230 --> 00:46:30,840
We don't have proof yet.

815
00:46:30,840 --> 00:46:32,560
Are you doing it or not?

816
00:46:32,560 --> 00:46:33,800
If not, I'll assign someone else.

817
00:46:33,800 --> 00:46:35,190
Wait! I will do it!

818
00:46:35,190 --> 00:46:36,470
Why would I say no?

819
00:46:40,000 --> 00:46:43,630
But my question is: why would he choose
this shop in particular?

820
00:46:43,630 --> 00:46:45,710
When you catch him, ask him yourself.

821
00:46:47,910 --> 00:46:48,520
What is it?

822
00:46:48,520 --> 00:46:50,120
A whistle.

823
00:46:50,120 --> 00:46:50,910
For what?

824
00:46:50,910 --> 00:46:51,560
For you to blow.

825
00:46:51,560 --> 00:46:54,390
If you see anything suspicious,
call for backup.

826
00:46:54,390 --> 00:46:54,870
Take it.

827
00:46:56,000 --> 00:46:57,080
Your shift is two hours.

828
00:46:57,080 --> 00:46:57,950
Then we'll switch.

829
00:47:39,150 --> 00:47:39,630
You?

830
00:47:42,950 --> 00:47:43,520
And you?

831
00:47:48,430 --> 00:47:50,280
A straight and a pair of sevens!

832
00:47:50,280 --> 00:47:51,040
Show me your cards.

833
00:47:52,320 --> 00:47:53,560
You need a pair of twos!

834
00:47:53,560 --> 00:47:55,360
You stink!

835
00:47:55,360 --> 00:47:56,150
Come on. Another round.

836
00:47:56,150 --> 00:47:57,000
Here you go, Chief.

837
00:47:59,870 --> 00:48:01,630
Wang Xiang is still on a stakeout.

838
00:48:02,280 --> 00:48:04,120
And? You wanna take his spot?

839
00:48:04,120 --> 00:48:04,870
No way.

840
00:48:06,040 --> 00:48:07,670
He's craving credit even in his dreams.

841
00:48:07,670 --> 00:48:08,630
I should wake him up.

842
00:48:09,190 --> 00:48:11,870
How dare a humble driver
stick his nose into my section!

843
00:48:12,630 --> 00:48:16,430
So what if you're from the bureau
or a captain in the police force?

844
00:48:16,430 --> 00:48:17,840
I'll tell you this.

845
00:48:17,840 --> 00:48:20,230
That won't work in Hualin Steel!

846
00:48:20,230 --> 00:48:21,150
You rock!

847
00:48:21,150 --> 00:48:22,120
Indeed!

848
00:48:22,120 --> 00:48:22,710
That's right.

849
00:48:23,910 --> 00:48:29,150
But, sir, what if
Dazhi did see the killer?

850
00:48:29,150 --> 00:48:30,870
Wang Xiang would never catch him.

851
00:48:31,950 --> 00:48:33,910
He meant to do that to save his job.

852
00:48:33,910 --> 00:48:35,390
Nice try.

853
00:48:38,600 --> 00:48:39,430
Liru!

854
00:48:40,630 --> 00:48:41,360
Liru!

855
00:48:46,870 --> 00:48:48,040
What took you so long?

856
00:48:48,560 --> 00:48:50,280
I rushed over
from your hospital.

857
00:48:50,280 --> 00:48:51,190
Why did you go there?

858
00:48:51,190 --> 00:48:52,520
We agreed to meet here.

859
00:48:53,040 --> 00:48:54,430
Something happened at work.

860
00:48:55,320 --> 00:48:58,000
My boss, Director Zhao, got cornered
by two workers in the canteen.

861
00:48:58,000 --> 00:48:58,630
They beat him up.

862
00:48:58,630 --> 00:49:00,360
He was bleeding all over.

863
00:49:00,360 --> 00:49:02,320
I had left,
but they called me back.

864
00:49:02,320 --> 00:49:03,910
Those guys in my office
couldn't do anything.

865
00:49:04,430 --> 00:49:06,120
I had to go back
and take care of the mess.

866
00:49:07,840 --> 00:49:08,560
I'm off duty.

867
00:49:08,560 --> 00:49:09,950
No more work-related topics.

868
00:49:11,190 --> 00:49:11,910
Sorry.

869
00:49:11,910 --> 00:49:13,080
You must be hungry.

870
00:49:13,910 --> 00:49:15,280
Did you just get one for yourself?

871
00:49:15,280 --> 00:49:16,320
Are we going to watch the movie or not?

872
00:49:17,190 --> 00:49:19,710
We are! I picked that one in particular.

873
00:49:19,710 --> 00:49:21,320
It's about a couple. Quite romantic.

874
00:49:22,120 --> 00:49:22,600
Give me a sec.

875
00:49:22,600 --> 00:49:23,390
I'm putting my bike here.

876
00:49:29,360 --> 00:49:30,560
Where did you
get that baked sweet potato?

877
00:49:30,560 --> 00:49:31,670
I'd like one, too.

878
00:49:48,600 --> 00:49:50,150
I picked the wrong one.

879
00:49:50,150 --> 00:49:53,710
I didn't know
they'd hook up like this.

880
00:49:53,710 --> 00:49:54,360
When I saw the name,

881
00:49:54,360 --> 00:49:55,710
I thought it'd be about Yu Dafu

882
00:49:55,710 --> 00:49:57,000
or Lin Huiyin.
[*Both are famous Chinese writers.]

883
00:49:58,320 --> 00:50:03,320
It is kinda sweet,
but the jumpy scenes make me dizzy.

884
00:50:05,870 --> 00:50:08,600
That actor looks a bit like you.

885
00:50:09,600 --> 00:50:10,280
Really?

886
00:50:12,600 --> 00:50:13,710
They always said

887
00:50:13,710 --> 00:50:17,950
I could be an actor,
but I chose academia.

888
00:50:23,600 --> 00:50:26,230
Did Xiang tell you about me?

889
00:50:27,840 --> 00:50:28,470
Who?

890
00:50:30,150 --> 00:50:31,080
Mr. Wang.

891
00:50:36,120 --> 00:50:37,910
Uh, not much, actually.

892
00:50:43,520 --> 00:50:44,670
Here's the thing.

893
00:50:45,670 --> 00:50:48,870
They say career before marriage.

894
00:50:50,230 --> 00:50:54,600
Right now, my career is rising.

895
00:50:55,280 --> 00:50:56,120
In Factory Affairs Office,

896
00:50:56,120 --> 00:50:58,000
I'm only under Director Zhao.

897
00:51:06,630 --> 00:51:08,600
Just say it. I can hear you.

898
00:51:11,560 --> 00:51:15,950
Freud once said
a psychologically healthy person

899
00:51:15,950 --> 00:51:17,360
should be able to do two things:

900
00:51:18,390 --> 00:51:20,800
"lieben und arbeiten",
to love and to work.

901
00:51:22,080 --> 00:51:23,280
In terms of work,

902
00:51:23,280 --> 00:51:25,470
I'm practically way ahead of others.

903
00:51:26,600 --> 00:51:28,910
So what I need is someone to love.

904
00:51:29,630 --> 00:51:31,040
Who's Freud?

905
00:51:32,080 --> 00:51:34,840
A scholar studying dreams.

906
00:51:35,520 --> 00:51:36,600
Did he get an apartment?

907
00:51:37,800 --> 00:51:39,760
No, he didn't work at our factory.

908
00:51:40,840 --> 00:51:41,800
Do you have one?

909
00:51:42,390 --> 00:51:43,230
Almost.

910
00:51:45,230 --> 00:51:48,630
I've had a serious discussion
about it with Zhao.

911
00:51:49,950 --> 00:51:51,360
You see,

912
00:51:51,360 --> 00:51:53,840
Mr. Song values talents.

913
00:51:53,840 --> 00:51:55,600
Based on my performance,

914
00:51:55,600 --> 00:51:57,320
I'll be in the next batch
of housing allocation.

915
00:52:06,000 --> 00:52:11,150
Liru, if you're dating someone,
what's your type?

916
00:52:15,520 --> 00:52:17,560
I prefer the mature ones.

917
00:52:17,560 --> 00:52:19,230
I excel at it.

918
00:52:22,520 --> 00:52:24,120
Why is that?

919
00:52:24,120 --> 00:52:25,320
They all say

920
00:52:25,320 --> 00:52:26,600
I look older than my age.

921
00:52:34,000 --> 00:52:35,800
Watch the movie. Don't move.

922
00:52:35,800 --> 00:52:36,630
It's your hair.

923
00:52:40,910 --> 00:52:42,470
What's there to watch anyway?

924
00:52:42,470 --> 00:52:44,520
I'm not interested in those guys.

925
00:52:48,780 --> 00:52:50,140
(Hualin Cinema)

926
00:52:50,150 --> 00:52:52,000
Liru, wait.

927
00:52:52,000 --> 00:52:52,800
I'll give you a ride.

928
00:53:00,190 --> 00:53:00,800
Hop on.

929
00:53:01,600 --> 00:53:03,040
You're going back to the dorm, right?

930
00:53:03,040 --> 00:53:04,000
I'm going the other way.

931
00:53:04,710 --> 00:53:06,280
The earth is round.

932
00:53:06,280 --> 00:53:08,080
Whichever way we take,
we'll get there eventually.

933
00:53:09,230 --> 00:53:10,600
Thanks, but no.

934
00:53:11,320 --> 00:53:13,520
How about we watch another movie later?

935
00:53:13,520 --> 00:53:15,150
We'll see. Bye.

936
00:53:24,280 --> 00:53:25,840
Who unplugged my valve core?

937
00:53:27,360 --> 00:53:28,670
Did you see it, sweet potato guy?

938
00:54:19,190 --> 00:54:20,120
Mr. Wang!

939
00:54:30,080 --> 00:54:31,430
Mr. Wang, are you hungry?

940
00:54:32,120 --> 00:54:34,430
How about we go and grab a bite?

941
00:54:37,520 --> 00:54:38,320
Stand up.

942
00:54:39,470 --> 00:54:40,080
Why?

943
00:54:45,150 --> 00:54:45,840
Now, turn.

944
00:54:50,710 --> 00:54:51,950
What's this about?

945
00:54:51,950 --> 00:54:53,150
How tall are you?

946
00:54:53,150 --> 00:54:53,840
1.8 meters.

947
00:54:54,600 --> 00:54:55,280
Really?

948
00:54:55,910 --> 00:54:58,910
1.785 without my shoes
and 1.8 with them.

949
00:55:00,280 --> 00:55:04,670
I mean,
you work in Factory Affairs Office.

950
00:55:05,560 --> 00:55:06,870
Why put on such a suit?

951
00:55:06,870 --> 00:55:07,710
What are you up to?

952
00:55:07,710 --> 00:55:09,120
Safety first, right?

953
00:55:09,630 --> 00:55:11,630
Suit up
before entering the Steel-making Shop.

954
00:55:12,430 --> 00:55:13,840
Aren't you cautious?

955
00:55:14,600 --> 00:55:15,280
Sit.

956
00:55:24,910 --> 00:55:26,470
How did you know where to find me?

957
00:55:26,470 --> 00:55:28,320
I went to Locomotives first.

958
00:55:28,320 --> 00:55:30,190
They said you had a meeting
with Security.

959
00:55:30,190 --> 00:55:33,760
When I got there,
they said to try my luck at the crane.

960
00:55:33,760 --> 00:55:35,910
And here you are,
waiting to be hooked.

961
00:55:37,560 --> 00:55:38,520
Say what?

962
00:55:39,670 --> 00:55:41,760
Hooked?

963
00:55:41,760 --> 00:55:42,670
I didn't mean that.

964
00:55:44,760 --> 00:55:45,870
This is a hook.

965
00:55:45,870 --> 00:55:46,360
Yeah.

966
00:55:49,320 --> 00:55:51,560
Also, I chose to expose myself.

967
00:55:51,560 --> 00:55:53,080
Otherwise, you wouldn't have found me.

968
00:55:53,080 --> 00:55:54,120
Yes, of course.

969
00:55:54,120 --> 00:55:55,560
You were so good at hiding.

970
00:55:55,560 --> 00:55:57,320
I... I put it the wrong way.

971
00:56:01,520 --> 00:56:03,080
Forget about that potato.

972
00:56:03,950 --> 00:56:06,230
Let's go out and talk over proper food.

973
00:56:06,230 --> 00:56:06,910
My treat.

974
00:56:08,670 --> 00:56:09,800
There's no such thing as a free meal.

975
00:56:11,390 --> 00:56:12,560
What's this about?

976
00:56:16,120 --> 00:56:17,800
It's about Liru and me.

977
00:56:18,470 --> 00:56:20,470
We need a push.

978
00:56:20,470 --> 00:56:21,630
I don't think so.

979
00:56:22,190 --> 00:56:23,320
Didn't you go to the cinema?

980
00:56:24,280 --> 00:56:25,190
Don't get me started.

981
00:56:26,600 --> 00:56:29,080
That movie was a bad choice.

982
00:56:29,080 --> 00:56:30,390
It's not about that.

983
00:56:33,630 --> 00:56:36,600
Mr. Wang, your help will be appreciated.

984
00:56:42,390 --> 00:56:43,430
Where did you get that booze?

985
00:56:43,950 --> 00:56:44,910
Mr. Song gave it to me.

986
00:56:50,430 --> 00:56:53,800
Song Yukun gave you this?

987
00:56:54,320 --> 00:56:58,150
A friend of mine taught
his son English for free.

988
00:56:58,150 --> 00:56:59,360
So he gave me that in return.

989
00:56:59,360 --> 00:57:00,800
He said it's quite aged.

990
00:57:01,760 --> 00:57:03,520
It's old enough to be your uncle.

991
00:57:04,390 --> 00:57:09,190
As long as Liru and I can get together,
it can be my grandpa. I mean it.

992
00:57:09,190 --> 00:57:10,520
Is your office busy lately?

993
00:57:11,560 --> 00:57:12,280
Why?

994
00:57:13,670 --> 00:57:14,560
If you're free,

995
00:57:14,560 --> 00:57:18,150
I could use your help with the
ongoing internal investigation.

996
00:57:18,950 --> 00:57:20,870
Sure. No problem.

997
00:57:21,520 --> 00:57:22,950
Your wish is my command.

998
00:57:24,430 --> 00:57:25,800
So Liru and I...?

999
00:57:27,280 --> 00:57:27,910
Wait for the good news.

1000
00:57:30,080 --> 00:57:31,120
Is it cooked?

1001
00:57:32,190 --> 00:57:33,120
Can I have a bite?

1002
00:57:39,190 --> 00:57:40,190
It tastes good!

1003
00:58:22,630 --> 00:58:25,840
Captain Ma,
this is Shen Mo's guidance counselor.

1004
00:58:26,430 --> 00:58:27,560
Ma Desheng, Criminal Police Unit.

1005
00:58:27,560 --> 00:58:28,230
Hello.

1006
00:58:28,230 --> 00:58:30,470
So, is that Shen Mo's stuff?

1007
00:58:32,280 --> 00:58:33,800
Hey, let's sit.

1008
00:58:35,040 --> 00:58:37,430
Shen Mo was from Songhe.

1009
00:58:38,150 --> 00:58:41,870
She seemed to be shy and quiet.

1010
00:58:42,560 --> 00:58:45,150
Academically, she was above average.

1011
00:58:45,150 --> 00:58:49,040
She didn't cause us too much trouble
except for

1012
00:58:49,600 --> 00:58:51,390
that incident earlier.

1013
00:58:54,320 --> 00:58:55,320
What happened?

1014
00:59:01,080 --> 00:59:02,120
Is it sensitive?

1015
00:59:29,360 --> 00:59:30,080
Where did you get these?

1016
00:59:30,950 --> 00:59:34,910
Those photos and that letter
were found on the bulletin board

1017
00:59:34,910 --> 00:59:39,120
outside the school canteen
in the morning on the 20th.

1018
00:59:39,120 --> 00:59:40,520
The letter also said

1019
00:59:41,520 --> 00:59:47,230
Shen Mo was an escort in a brothel,

1020
00:59:47,230 --> 00:59:49,000
drinking and sleeping with her clients.

1021
00:59:49,000 --> 00:59:50,150
Why didn't you call the police?

1022
00:59:52,000 --> 00:59:56,080
Our school was concerned
about our reputation.

1023
01:00:04,150 --> 01:00:06,710
I had heard such rumors
from other students.

1024
01:00:06,840 --> 01:00:08,950
Her life outside campus
seemed to be complicated.

1025
01:00:09,430 --> 01:00:11,760
And there was this boy
who came all the time.

1026
01:00:12,040 --> 01:00:12,760
Yes. That's right.

1027
01:00:12,760 --> 01:00:14,950
He even wrote a letter of apology
in the Dean's Office.

1028
01:00:45,600 --> 01:00:47,430
How about we call it a day, Mr. Wang?

1029
01:00:48,430 --> 01:00:50,430
I need to go back to my office
in case they need me.

1030
01:00:55,600 --> 01:00:57,630
What's this mess?

1031
01:01:00,710 --> 01:01:01,280
Go easy.

1032
01:01:01,280 --> 01:01:02,630
Don't ruin my pants.

1033
01:01:07,040 --> 01:01:07,870
Shed a light.

1034
01:01:09,150 --> 01:01:09,760
Over there.

1035
01:01:10,320 --> 01:01:11,190
Keep going!

1036
01:01:11,190 --> 01:01:12,080
This is the farthest I can go.

1037
01:01:12,950 --> 01:01:14,190
That's it. Yeah.

1038
01:01:14,190 --> 01:01:15,190
Don't move. That's the one.

1039
01:01:52,760 --> 01:01:53,600
Mr. Wang!

1040
01:01:54,470 --> 01:01:55,670
Mr. Wang!

1041
01:01:55,670 --> 01:01:56,560
Right here.

1042
01:01:57,150 --> 01:01:58,520
Bad news, Mr. Wang!

1043
01:01:58,520 --> 01:01:59,390
What's wrong?

1044
01:01:59,910 --> 01:02:02,710
Your wife said on the phone
that the police took your son away!

1045
01:02:05,180 --> 01:02:07,180
(Hualin Public Security Bureau)

1046
01:02:08,340 --> 01:02:11,940
(The police should serve the people.)

1047
01:02:33,430 --> 01:02:34,190
What's wrong?

1048
01:02:35,910 --> 01:02:37,600
Answer my question!

1049
01:02:37,600 --> 01:02:39,600
Mr. Wang, calm down.

1050
01:02:40,560 --> 01:02:43,190
We brought him in
for asking him something about a case.

1051
01:02:43,190 --> 01:02:44,910
Now, we're done. He can go home.

1052
01:02:46,230 --> 01:02:47,120
What case?

1053
01:02:48,040 --> 01:02:49,280
What is it?

1054
01:02:49,280 --> 01:02:50,320
Say it!

1055
01:02:53,870 --> 01:02:54,670
Stop!

1056
01:02:55,870 --> 01:02:57,150
Did I say you can leave?

1057
01:02:58,430 --> 01:03:00,600
Hey, is Captain Ma in his office?

1058
01:03:02,430 --> 01:03:03,760
Keep an eye on him, will you?

1059
01:03:06,670 --> 01:03:07,320
Captain Ma,

1060
01:03:08,040 --> 01:03:09,190
I thought you went out.

1061
01:03:09,710 --> 01:03:10,800
I'm glad you're here.

1062
01:03:13,670 --> 01:03:15,600
What happened to my son, Yang,

1063
01:03:15,600 --> 01:03:16,120
Captain Ma?

1064
01:03:26,190 --> 01:03:27,320
Is Wang Yang your son?

1065
01:03:28,120 --> 01:03:28,710
Yeah.

1066
01:03:30,600 --> 01:03:32,280
He was dating this girl, Shen Mo.

1067
01:03:32,280 --> 01:03:33,230
You know that?

1068
01:03:34,630 --> 01:03:35,430
Shen Mo?

1069
01:03:36,710 --> 01:03:38,390
I don't know
they were seeing each other.

1070
01:03:39,080 --> 01:03:40,230
You can ask him when you get back.

1071
01:03:40,230 --> 01:03:41,040
I'm done here.

1072
01:03:41,950 --> 01:03:44,630
Tell your son
he can't get out of town these days.

1073
01:03:45,000 --> 01:03:46,710
We might bring him in
for questioning again.

1074
01:03:51,560 --> 01:03:52,040
I see.

1075
01:03:54,910 --> 01:03:55,520
Sir,

1076
01:03:57,360 --> 01:03:58,870
I found something in the factory...

1077
01:03:58,870 --> 01:04:03,000
Mr. Wang,
you shouldn't come here again.

1078
01:04:04,320 --> 01:04:06,600
And stay away from this case.

1079
01:04:07,910 --> 01:04:08,800
Your job is to drive trains.

1080
01:04:13,040 --> 01:04:14,560
But I'm your Watson, right?

1081
01:04:16,040 --> 01:04:17,190
Stories aren't reality.

1082
01:04:19,870 --> 01:04:20,910
I prefer Raymond Chandler.
[*A renowned American crime writer.]

1083
01:04:21,760 --> 01:04:23,600
Guodong, show Mr. Wang out.

1084
01:04:24,800 --> 01:04:26,390
Chan... Chandler who?

1085
01:04:26,390 --> 01:04:27,320
Mr. Wang.

1086
01:04:28,120 --> 01:04:28,870
Let's go.

1087
01:04:29,430 --> 01:04:30,000
Sure.

1088
01:04:32,560 --> 01:04:33,360
Sir, I...

1089
01:04:34,560 --> 01:04:35,080
Coming.

1090
01:05:01,120 --> 01:05:02,360
Look what you've done!

1091
01:05:03,560 --> 01:05:04,800
You even had a girlfriend?

1092
01:05:05,670 --> 01:05:06,950
What happened to her?

1093
01:05:09,000 --> 01:05:10,560
I have said everything to the police.

1094
01:05:12,390 --> 01:05:13,670
She died, you know that?

1095
01:05:15,670 --> 01:05:19,630
I told you not to work at the
wrong place, but you didn't listen.

1096
01:05:21,390 --> 01:05:24,800
When we get home, you're grounded

1097
01:05:26,120 --> 01:05:27,390
until this case is solved.

1098
01:05:28,040 --> 01:05:29,000
You can't go out before that.

1099
01:05:35,360 --> 01:05:36,230
Stop!

1100
01:05:39,760 --> 01:05:41,520
You can't run away from the problem!

1101
01:05:42,520 --> 01:05:44,470
You can tell me whatever happened.

1102
01:06:03,040 --> 01:06:03,800
Where's Yang?

1103
01:06:04,560 --> 01:06:05,630
Why didn't he come back with you?

1104
01:06:05,630 --> 01:06:08,120
He'll be back in no time.

1105
01:06:08,800 --> 01:06:09,950
What did the police say?

1106
01:06:09,950 --> 01:06:11,120
Nothing really. It's fine.

1107
01:06:12,150 --> 01:06:13,840
Really? But why did the police need him?

1108
01:06:14,520 --> 01:06:15,320
Hey, wait!

1109
01:06:15,320 --> 01:06:16,870
I'm... I'm talking to you!

1110
01:06:21,080 --> 01:06:24,320
I called you to pick up my son.

1111
01:06:24,320 --> 01:06:25,800
Where is he now?

1112
01:06:26,670 --> 01:06:27,910
My heart is racing!

1113
01:06:27,910 --> 01:06:29,560
Are you sure he's OK?

1114
01:06:29,560 --> 01:06:30,600
Don't fool me.

1115
01:06:31,840 --> 01:06:32,600
He's my son, too.

1116
01:06:32,600 --> 01:06:34,040
I won't let anything happen to him.

1117
01:06:34,040 --> 01:06:35,520
When will he get back?

1118
01:06:35,520 --> 01:06:36,630
Stop following me around.

1119
01:06:36,630 --> 01:06:37,560
You're giving me a headache!

1120
01:06:37,560 --> 01:06:38,230
I need to lie down.

1121
01:06:40,760 --> 01:06:42,150
I'm having one, too!

1122
01:07:14,630 --> 01:07:15,360
Quit it.

1123
01:07:15,360 --> 01:07:19,020
(ME's Office)

1124
01:07:19,840 --> 01:07:21,840
Captain, they're Shen Mo's next of kin.

1125
01:07:21,840 --> 01:07:23,760
They came from Songhe
for the identification.

1126
01:07:23,760 --> 01:07:25,150
Head of the Criminal Police Unit,

1127
01:07:25,150 --> 01:07:26,150
Ma Desheng.

1128
01:07:26,150 --> 01:07:26,630
Hello.

1129
01:07:28,000 --> 01:07:29,230
Captain Ma,

1130
01:07:29,670 --> 01:07:33,870
I was born here, too,
and worked in the city

1131
01:07:33,870 --> 01:07:35,910
a few years back.

1132
01:07:35,910 --> 01:07:38,870
I've got connections in your bureau.

1133
01:07:40,230 --> 01:07:40,910
Are you done?

1134
01:07:41,430 --> 01:07:43,120
Li Qun, bring him to the office.

1135
01:07:43,870 --> 01:07:44,390
This way, please.

1136
01:07:45,470 --> 01:07:46,600
Is there anything else?

1137
01:07:46,600 --> 01:07:49,000
The investigation is still ongoing.

1138
01:07:49,000 --> 01:07:51,190
I need to ask you
about Shen Mo's recent life.

1139
01:07:52,360 --> 01:07:55,760
Well, we've booked return tickets.

1140
01:07:55,760 --> 01:07:57,950
The train waits for no men.

1141
01:07:57,950 --> 01:07:59,120
I'm quite busy.

1142
01:07:59,120 --> 01:08:01,520
I need to go back to Songhe.

1143
01:08:01,520 --> 01:08:03,280
It's not like we can do it
on the train, right?

1144
01:08:04,520 --> 01:08:05,190
We're all busy.

1145
01:08:07,360 --> 01:08:08,390
OK.

1146
01:08:08,390 --> 01:08:10,280
We'll comply.

1147
01:08:12,000 --> 01:08:13,000
Stop crying.

1148
01:08:16,160 --> 01:08:16,720
Let's go.

1149
01:08:29,680 --> 01:08:33,000
Captain, that guy strikes me as odd.

1150
01:08:33,000 --> 01:08:33,910
How so?

1151
01:08:34,600 --> 01:08:36,390
He reminds me of you.

1152
01:08:37,200 --> 01:08:38,310
No way!

1153
01:08:39,000 --> 01:08:41,560
I mean he doesn't look like her father.

1154
01:08:41,560 --> 01:08:42,910
That's because he isn't.

1155
01:08:42,910 --> 01:08:43,600
He's her uncle.

1156
01:08:44,600 --> 01:08:45,950
He adopted Shen Mo.

1157
01:08:46,900 --> 01:08:49,740
(The police should serve the people.)

1158
01:08:53,560 --> 01:08:54,240
Come here.

1159
01:08:56,350 --> 01:08:56,870
Take a look.

1160
01:08:57,790 --> 01:08:58,830
You've got sharp eyes.

1161
01:08:58,830 --> 01:08:59,430
Look at this.

1162
01:08:59,430 --> 01:09:02,200
There are two characters on the
thermos next to the nightstand.

1163
01:09:03,040 --> 01:09:04,160
What's the last one?

1164
01:09:05,720 --> 01:09:07,520
The paint's scraped off.

1165
01:09:07,520 --> 01:09:09,600
I know. That's why I need your help.

1166
01:09:12,910 --> 01:09:14,680
"Hui". It's "Hui".

1167
01:09:15,430 --> 01:09:16,040
Am I right?

1168
01:09:18,870 --> 01:09:20,680
Captain Ma,
Director Zhu is calling for a meeting.

1169
01:09:23,350 --> 01:09:24,470
This late?

1170
01:09:26,870 --> 01:09:27,830
Here you go.

1171
01:09:27,830 --> 01:09:29,120
Eat it after the meeting.

1172
01:09:29,120 --> 01:09:31,350
I need water. I'm thirsty.

1173
01:09:31,350 --> 01:09:32,720
It's empty.

1174
01:09:32,720 --> 01:09:33,680
Come on!

1175
01:10:01,160 --> 01:10:02,040
Director.

1176
01:10:02,040 --> 01:10:02,560
Take a seat.

1177
01:10:08,270 --> 01:10:08,790
Sir...

1178
01:10:10,910 --> 01:10:13,910
That so-called Hong Kong businessman is
actually from Zhanjiang, Guangdong.

1179
01:10:13,910 --> 01:10:15,240
His company is registered
in Hong Kong, China.

1180
01:10:15,750 --> 01:10:19,000
He contacted his driver on the fifth,
then he's gone radio silent since.

1181
01:10:19,680 --> 01:10:20,910
Before he disappeared,
he received a bank draft

1182
01:10:20,910 --> 01:10:22,160
worth 800 grand from Hualin Steel.

1183
01:10:22,430 --> 01:10:24,470
The bank said
the money had been withdrawn,

1184
01:10:24,640 --> 01:10:27,470
Now, we believe this case might
be more than a simple fraud.

1185
01:10:29,000 --> 01:10:30,390
Do you know any of that,

1186
01:10:30,390 --> 01:10:31,040
Ma Desheng?

1187
01:10:33,600 --> 01:10:35,720
Aren't you their captain?

1188
01:10:35,720 --> 01:10:37,080
I'm working around the clock.

1189
01:10:37,080 --> 01:10:38,910
I need results!

1190
01:10:39,240 --> 01:10:41,000
The dismemberment case
is no longer your concern.

1191
01:10:41,000 --> 01:10:42,120
Police Corps will take over.

1192
01:10:42,120 --> 01:10:45,750
Your priority now is
to follow the money.

1193
01:10:46,310 --> 01:10:48,720
Find out who withdrew it.

1194
01:10:48,720 --> 01:10:50,200
Sure, sure.

1195
01:10:50,200 --> 01:10:51,240
Of course.

1196
01:10:51,240 --> 01:10:53,520
I'll do it, but not now.

1197
01:10:53,520 --> 01:10:55,040
Wait until I get back from Songhe.

1198
01:10:55,040 --> 01:10:56,080
Why are you going there?

1199
01:10:56,600 --> 01:10:59,600
The one who took nude photos of Shen Mo
and wrote the anonymous letter

1200
01:10:59,600 --> 01:11:01,430
must be someone she knew.

1201
01:11:01,430 --> 01:11:02,270
I have to go there.

1202
01:11:02,270 --> 01:11:03,120
Alone.

1203
01:11:03,120 --> 01:11:05,270
I need to check with her family again.

1204
01:11:05,270 --> 01:11:07,560
Ma Desheng,
did you not hear what I just said?

1205
01:11:07,560 --> 01:11:08,750
I can't do anything else.

1206
01:11:09,720 --> 01:11:11,310
Her remains are right there!

1207
01:11:12,200 --> 01:11:13,270
But we're so close to solving that case.

1208
01:11:13,270 --> 01:11:14,830
What if the suspect got away?

1209
01:11:14,830 --> 01:11:19,720
Ma Desheng, as a police officer, you
have to do your best in every single case!

1210
01:11:19,720 --> 01:11:21,240
Yes, I am!

1211
01:11:21,240 --> 01:11:22,430
So I have to catch that murderer!

1212
01:11:24,160 --> 01:11:27,750
Sir, regarding that missing businessman,

1213
01:11:27,750 --> 01:11:28,790
I've got a theory.

1214
01:11:29,470 --> 01:11:33,160
I can fill in for Captain
Ma to trace the money.

1215
01:11:33,160 --> 01:11:34,160
Enough.

1216
01:11:34,160 --> 01:11:35,200
This has nothing to do with you.

1217
01:11:35,200 --> 01:11:36,390
Why?

1218
01:11:36,390 --> 01:11:37,680
He's one of us, too.

1219
01:11:48,220 --> 01:11:52,460
(The police should serve the people.)

1220
01:12:00,350 --> 01:12:01,120
Your wallet!

1221
01:12:05,350 --> 01:12:06,240
It's late.

1222
01:12:06,240 --> 01:12:07,310
Are you driving there alone?

1223
01:12:07,310 --> 01:12:07,680
Why?

1224
01:12:07,680 --> 01:12:09,200
Are you coming with me?

1225
01:12:09,200 --> 01:12:10,310
Get in. I'll be your driver.

1226
01:12:11,000 --> 01:12:12,830
You stay and help Li Qun
trace the money.

1227
01:12:12,830 --> 01:12:13,750
I'm fine.

1228
01:12:13,750 --> 01:12:15,000
I'll be back tomorrow morning.

1229
01:12:16,200 --> 01:12:17,910
Don't bring that guy up.

1230
01:12:18,470 --> 01:12:19,750
You saw what he was like just now.

1231
01:12:20,430 --> 01:12:21,790
He meant to step in.

1232
01:12:21,790 --> 01:12:23,000
Who does he think he is?

1233
01:12:23,000 --> 01:12:24,270
That rat!

1234
01:12:24,270 --> 01:12:25,830
He took the bullet for me.

1235
01:12:25,830 --> 01:12:27,080
Alright. Gotta go.

1236
01:12:30,080 --> 01:12:30,910
Got a cigarette?

1237
01:12:30,910 --> 01:12:32,560
Why? Are you done quitting it?

1238
01:12:35,750 --> 01:12:36,430
Never mind.

